photos.title: Lake Nicaragua
photos.description: The other side of the lake.

photos.title: Chill Out
photos.description: We had some smoothies at a place not far away, and stuck around to enjoy the ambiance before the rain came.

photos.title: Cross Dress Party
photos.description: Every Saturday, men wear dresses. It makes people happy.

photos.title: Cute Couple
photos.description: Eli's great. But that guy, what an ass ;-)

photos.title: The Summit
photos.description: climbed to the top of a volcano... Pretty much saw clouds. Oh well.

photos.title: People Covered By Tarp
photos.description: These folks were all covering up because the lake was turbulent enough to make some splashing happen. Fortunately, at the very very front of the boat, I was relatively dry, and had a rain jacket.

photos.title: Cloud Explosion
photos.description: At the end of the day the sort of lighting wasn't uncommon due to the direction of the sun, and us pretty much being in a crater.

photos.title: Canada Dry
photos.description: Never seen this in a glass bottle.

photos.title: Santa Cruz Village
photos.description: The village up on the hill.

photos.title: The Dump
photos.description: Most of this stuff is to get burned. I bet this is 150 Meters above lake level, and is on the road down to Santa Cruz. Some dogs chased me.

photos.title: Switchback
photos.description: This is one of the turns, but as you can see, there was a fairly recent landslide.
